cs.NI, cs.AR, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.IT 

The paper discusses the performance of Named Data Networking (NDN) in wireless access networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the architectural enhancements needed to support mobility, which falls under the category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the current NDN architecture, which is related to performance evaluation and analysis, falling under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the decoupling of applications from transport semantics, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing, falling under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the interaction between ICN and mobility of consuming and producing applications, which is related to information theory, falling under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
